FBIS3-19287 "drweu050aa_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-050 Document Type:Daily Report 11 Mar 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS UN Asks Belgium To Man Tuzla Control Towers BR1103132494 Antwerpen GAZET VAN ANTWERPEN 11 Mar 94 p 1 BR1103132494 Antwerpen GAZET VAN ANTWERPEN 11 Mar 94 p 1 Article Type:BFN [Report by Paul Verbraecken: "United Nations Requests Belgian Military for Tuzla Airport--Air Force To Man Control Towers of Disputed Airport"] [Excerpt] On his way to Rwanda, Defense Minister Delcroix confirmed on Thursday [10 March] that the United Nations had formally requested Belgian military support for the reopening of Tuzla airport in Bosnia. The United Nations requests a contingent of 25 Belgian Air Force staff to man the control towers of this disputed airport. There is no mention of pilots.
